cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY 

This paper discusses the development of a citation-based indicator for interdisciplinarity in journals. The paper focuses on network indicators, journal indicators, and recently proposed measures for interdisciplinarity. The study uses the Journal Citation Reports of the (Social) Science Citation Index 2008, which suggests that the paper is related to information retrieval (cs.IR), digital libraries (cs.DL), social and information networks (cs.SI), systems and control (cs.SD), and computers and society (cs.CY). However, given the focus on journal indicators and citation networks, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
